<subSubSection pageId="4" pageNumber="555" type="discussion">
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,629,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,332,881,906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Discussion.</emphasis>
Two varieties of 
<taxonomicName box="[534,654,881,905]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis box="[534,654,881,905]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P. torridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
were described by 
<bibRefCitation author="Breddin" box="[879,1055,881,906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" refString="Breddin, G. (1906) Rhynchotographische Beitrage. (Zweites Stuck.) Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 25 (5 - 7), 188 - 200." type="journal article" year="1906">
Breddin (
<number box="[986,1047,881,906]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1906.0">1906</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Both names were proposed with incorrect gender ending; since they are combined with the masculine generic name 
<taxonomicName authority="Burmeister, 1835" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1835" box="[1100,1432,917,942]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="genus">
<emphasis box="[1100,1226,917,941]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Pachycoris</emphasis>
Burmeister, 
<number box="[1373,1432,917,942]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1835.0">1835</number>
</taxonomicName>
, their gender ending is hereby changed to masculine following 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[847,1144,953,978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">
<collectionCode box="[847,912,954,978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">ICZN</collectionCode>
(
<number box="[927,987,954,978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1999.0">1999</number>
, Article 
<number box="[1083,1137,954,978]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="34.2">34.2</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
. Both names are available and deemed to be of subspecific rank according to 
<bibRefCitation author="ICZN" box="[733,1131,989,1014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" refString="ICZN (1999) International Code of Zoological Nomenclature. Fourth edition. International Trust for Zoological Nomenclature, London, 306 pp." type="book" year="1999">
<collectionCode box="[733,799,990,1014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">ICZN</collectionCode>
(
<number box="[815,875,990,1014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1999.0">1999</number>
, Articles 
<number box="[984,1035,990,1014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="10.2">10.2</number>
, 45.6.4)
</bibRefCitation>
. The depository of its 
<typeStatus box="[1388,1436,990,1014]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">type</typeStatus>
material has remained unknown so far. For 
<taxonomicName box="[636,1061,1025,1049]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="torridus" variety="moestissimus">
<emphasis box="[636,858,1025,1049]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Pachycoris torridus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[913,1061,1026,1049]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">moestissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, proposed for an uniformly black form lacking dorsal markings, a 
<typeStatus box="[512,560,1062,1086]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">type</typeStatus>
locality (“Sta. 
<taxonomicName box="[727,838,1061,1086]" class="Polyplacophora" family="Mopaliidae" genus="Catharina" higherTaxonomySource="GBIF" kingdom="Animalia" order="Neoloricata" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Mollusca" rank="genus">Catharina</taxonomicName>
” = Santa Catarina state of South 
<collectingCountry box="[1206,1276,1061,1086]" name="Brazil" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Brazil</collectingCountry>
) was given. A single specimen from the same locality was located among unidentified specimens originating from Breddin’s collection deposited in the 
<collectionCode box="[462,524,1134,1158]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">SDEI</collectionCode>
and designated as 
<typeStatus box="[746,853,1133,1158]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">lectotype</typeStatus>
. No 
<typeStatus box="[909,957,1134,1158]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">type</typeStatus>
locality was specified for 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="variety" species="torridus" variety="laetissimus">
<emphasis box="[1265,1385,1133,1157]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P. torridus</emphasis>
var. 
<emphasis box="[151,275,1169,1193]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">laetissimus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
, an uniformly “rusty yellow” (“rostgelb”) form with black markings at anterior and lateral margins and cicatrices of pronotum; 
<bibRefCitation author="Breddin" box="[417,588,1205,1230]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" refString="Breddin, G. (1906) Rhynchotographische Beitrage. (Zweites Stuck.) Wiener Entomologische Zeitung, 25 (5 - 7), 188 - 200." type="journal article" year="1906">
Breddin (
<number box="[522,580,1205,1230]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1906.0">1906</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
stated that it was distributed in South 
<collectingCountry box="[1015,1111,1205,1230]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">America</collectingCountry>
from 
<collectingCountry box="[1179,1283,1206,1230]" name="Paraguay" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Paraguay</collectingCountry>
to 
<collectingCountry box="[1318,1431,1205,1230]" name="Colombia" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Colombia</collectingCountry>
, but he did not have specimens from Central 
<collectingCountry box="[682,782,1241,1266]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">America</collectingCountry>
. From among the 
<specimenCount box="[1002,1159,1241,1266]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" type="generic">
<number box="[1002,1030,1242,1266]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="80.0">80</number>
specimens
</specimenCount>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[1204,1326,1241,1265]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis box="[1204,1326,1241,1265]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P. torridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
found in Breddin’s collection we selected for 
<typeStatus box="[561,663,1277,1302]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">lectotype</typeStatus>
the one that fits the original description the best.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,629,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">
These varieties have not been treated subsequently by any authors except 
<bibRefCitation author="Kirkaldy" box="[1026,1207,1313,1338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" refString="Kirkaldy, G. W. (1909) Catalogue of the Hemiptera (Heteroptera) with biological and anatomical references, lists of foodplants and parasites, etc. Vol. I. Cimicidae. F. L. Dames, Berlin, xl + 392 pp." type="book" year="1909">
Kirkaldy (
<number box="[1141,1199,1314,1338]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1909.0">1909</number>
)
</bibRefCitation>
who placed them as varieties of 
<taxonomicName authority="Burmeister, 1835" authorityName="Burmeister" authorityYear="1835" box="[283,579,1349,1374]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis box="[283,297,1350,1373]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[311,375,1349,1373]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">klugii</emphasis>
Burmeister, 
<number box="[520,579,1349,1374]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1835.0">1835</number>
</taxonomicName>
. The distribution of 
<taxonomicName box="[807,899,1349,1373]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="klugii">
<emphasis box="[807,821,1350,1373]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P</emphasis>
. 
<emphasis box="[835,899,1349,1373]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">klugii</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is restricted to 
<collectingCountry box="[1072,1158,1349,1374]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Mexico</collectingCountry>
and, to a limited degree, some countries south of 
<collectingCountry box="[450,535,1385,1410]" name="Mexico" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Mexico</collectingCountry>
in Central 
<collectingCountry box="[680,780,1385,1410]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">America</collectingCountry>
. Because the two varieties were described from South 
<collectingCountry box="[151,250,1421,1446]" name="United States of America" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">America</collectingCountry>
, Kirkaldy’s (
<number box="[394,453,1422,1446]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1909.0">1909</number>
) action was clearly in error.
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,629,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">
<taxonomicName box="[199,423,1457,1481]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis box="[199,423,1457,1481]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Pachycoris torridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
is a highly polychromatic species; the 
<typeStatus box="[866,980,1457,1482]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">lectotypes</typeStatus>
of both varieties are conspecific with 
<taxonomicName class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P. torridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
and do not merit recognition even at subspecies level, therefore we recognize them as 
<emphasis bold="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">new junior subjective synonyms</emphasis>
of 
<taxonomicName box="[439,558,1529,1553]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis box="[439,558,1529,1553]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">P. torridus</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
. A photo of another common variety and a brief review of the bionomics of this species were provided by Eger 
<emphasis box="[549,605,1565,1589]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">et al.</emphasis>
(
<number box="[620,681,1565,1590]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="2015.0">2015</number>
).
</paragraph>
<paragraph blockId="4.[151,1436,629,1626]" box="[199,1204,1601,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">
<emphasis bold="true" box="[199,380,1601,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Current status.</emphasis>
New junior subjective synonyms of 
<taxonomicName authority="Scopoli, 1772" authorityName="Scopoli" authorityYear="1772" box="[792,1200,1601,1626]" class="Insecta" family="Scutelleridae" genus="Pachycoris" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hemiptera" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="torridus">
<emphasis box="[792,1015,1601,1625]" italics="true" pageId="4" pageNumber="555">Pachycoris torridus</emphasis>
(Scopoli, 
<number box="[1131,1191,1602,1626]" pageId="4" pageNumber="555" value="1772.0">1772</number>
)
</taxonomicName>
.
</paragraph>
